Description: Pacific Surf Designs is a designing and manufacturing company that develops sheet wave surfing attractions for its clients.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: We have years of experience designing, manufacturing, and installing sheet wave surfing attractions for the waterpark, entertainment, and leisure industries. What is a sheet wave? We use large axial-flow pumps to send 2-3 inches of water at ~25-30mph over a padded ride surface creating a rideable sheet of water. The result is an endless wave that allows riders to perform maneuvers similar to those in surfing, skateboarding, and other board sports.  Four different product lines are available catering to different types of operators and venues.  What is the value proposition our products offer to our customers? 1. attracts hard-to-capture 10-35 year olds 2. creates repeat riders through noticeable skill improvements with each ride 3. riders bring friends - captive audience 4. generates revenue through ticket sales + food and beverage, private lessons/events/parties, and digital souvenirs 5. smaller footprint, lower construction and ownership costs compared to other water attractions

Description: The Gazette-Democrat is an newspaper.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: The Gazette Democrat served one of Illinois' most important communities at a time when the region was dense with wilderness. Through the 150 years that followed, the Jonesboro Gazette evolved into what is now The Gazette Democrat. Today's newspaper represents past consolidations of the Jonesboro Gazette, the Anna Democrat, Anna Talk, and Cobden Review. By the time the newspaper was established, Jonesboro was the hub of regional activity in a changing culture that had largely left behind its ways of a frontier settlement. By 1858, another newspaper, The Democrat, was established in Jonesboro, but soon moved to Anna where it was renamed The Anna Democrat.

Data-driven parenting. StoryTold narrows generation gap providing a unique hand-picked content feed tailored to one’s interests and situation. Every piece of content (story prompts, tips, lessons, articles, etc) is crowdsourced by a dozen of diverse US parents and family psychologists through StoryTold collaboration framework.

The goal of 321Lend is to build an online financial community that connects creditworthy borrowers with savvy investors in order to facilitate better lending rates and lower loan default rates by continuously innovating its web application and business strategies.  The Company has made significant progress with building its platform and laying the foundation to launch its business. The Company is currently near completion and with funding, will be able to operate as a peer to peer lending platform.   Though the Peer-to-Peer lending industry is one of the fastest growing industry  in the US estimated to be about $5B with CAGR of 100%+, it still covers only 1% of total credit card market of $669B. Since 321Lend is founded in March 2014, the company achieved the following: - Completed the front end of its website to attract potential borrowers and lenders  - Near completion of its back end platform to automate transactions - Built its proprietary interest rating model - Prepared compliance documents such as FCRA, FDCA, TILA, ECOA, and others - Secured relationship with banking partner to originate loans - Final discussion with credit rating agency Front end of website is launched at (http://www.321lend.com) and it is receiving numerous inquires from both lenders and borrowers.
Founders: Chris Wu, Johnny Tong, Shin Hwang

Description: Leading provider of contract oil and gas drilling services.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Houston Area, Southern US
Full Description: Todco is a leading provider of contract oil and gas drilling services, primarily in the U.S. Gulf of Mexico shallow water and inland marine region, an area that they refer to as the U.S. Gulf Coast. They have the largest fleet of drilling rigs in the U.S. Gulf Coast and believe that, as a result of their leading position and geographic focus, they are well-positioned to benefit from the potential increased drilling activity for natural gas in this region. They own, have partial ownership in or operate a fleet of 70 drilling rigs. Their U.S. Gulf Coast jackup fleet consists of 19 rigs, including independent leg cantilever jackup rigs, mat-supported cantilever jackup rigs and mat-supported slot-type jackup rigs that drill in water depths up to 250 feet. Their U.S. Gulf Coast drilling barge fleet consists of 30 rigs, including posted and conventional barges that operate in inland waters, bays and coastal transition zones. They own three submersible drilling rigs located in the U.S. Gulf Coast, two jackup rigs and a platform rig located in Trinidad and nine land rigs as well as three lake barges located in Venezuela. Additionally, they have one independent leg cantilever jackup rig being mobilized to Venezuela that is scheduled to begin operating in mid-December 2003. They also have two mat-supported cantilever jackup rigs working in Mexico.
